				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Pass the Bag" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Pass the Bag is an educational game for three to eight players designed to teach colors, shapes and sizes. Components include a plastic bag with one see-through side, four collecting cards and 40 wooden pieces in five shapes, each in two sizes, with four pieces of each size in red, yellow, blue and green.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With up to four players, each player takes a card. Players take turns holding the bag with the clear side facing away (so the other players can see the pieces inside). The current player selects a piece by touch that matches a piece of the right size and shape on his card. If it is the right color, he places it on his card. The first to fill his card wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A variant for any number of players is to place up to three cards in the center of the table. Players try to select by touch a piece that matches any piece on any card. A player who draws one of the right color places it on a card. Otherwise, he keeps the piece. When the bag is empty, the player with the fewest pieces in front of him wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players are encouraged to use words, noises, gestures and expressions to mislead the active player into thinking he is touching the correct (or incorrect) color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
